Former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan spoke to CNN's Cristiane Amanpour about his recent axing, and the political turmoil within the ANC since President Jacob Zuma's Cabinet reshuffle. The interview was aired on Thursday.&nbsp;Gordhan appeared to duck the hard questions and, rather diplomatically, speaks about collective leadership and responsibility in turning around the ANC's fortunes.&nbsp; READ ALSO: Gordhan praises Ramaphosa, backs State Capture inquiry&nbsp;He also looked ahead to the 2019 elections and speaks fondly of Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa. Watch below for more.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.